properties.name: Bridge #2- Front and Spruce st
properties.description: Posted by NewbieexplorersFront ST and Spruce street, san diegothis suspension bridge swings and sways underfoot. The canyon floor, lying 70-feet below, is lined eucalyptus, pepper and palm trees. This unique structure was built in 1912 by San Diego city engineer Edwin Capps. The bridge connected Spruce Street inhabitants with the downtown trolley line. These days, the bridge serves as a pleasant respite from the traffic-dominated streets of San Diego.
